There is a ever growing rumour of certain parts of High Speed 2 (HS2) to be scrapped!
  Railway News   Aug 25, 2021   0   29  Add to Reading List
Currently as this post has been made the Western Part of HS2 (London-Birmingham-Manchester) is still going ahead although there is rumour that Eastern sections will not be going ahead.
There has been claims of the Government declining to make any commitment on Phase 2b of HS2 towards the East Midlands and Yorkshire.
The Eastern section was to be a time saver of those travelling via big stations, although there is already enough word saying it's not much of a deal as it will only be saving 8 minutes.
Let us know your opinions on HS2, and do you think it will be going all the way, or just part of the project? Let us know!
Thank you for taking the time to read this post, enjoy your day!
